  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIf long tap to a message to call reaction menu and scroll it without lifting your finger from the screen, the message disappears from the chat history. If after that open any other tab (e.g. browser), send the app to background and open the app again, all disappeared messages will appear with the reaction menu and will be overlaid to the last screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![ezgif com-resize (17)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/89920459-b863a100-dbfc-11ea-9618-0d1dec6121a8.gif)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open chat (any type)\r\n- Send several messages (all types)\r\n- Long tap to any message and scroll without lifting your finger from the screen\r\n- Open Browser view\r\n- Send the app to background\r\n- Open Status\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: Nightly 11/08\r\n- Operating System: Android 8,10",
